<body>
<h1>To Kill a Mockingbird</h1>
<h2>by Harper Lee</h2><img src="book-cover.jpg" alt="To Kill a Mockingbird book cover">

<h2>Summary</h2>
    <p>To Kill a Mockingbird is a novel by Harper Lee, published in 1960. It is set in the fictional town of Maycomb, Alabama, during the Great Depression. The story is told from the perspective of a young girl named Scout, whose father, Atticus Finch, is a lawyer defending a black man accused of a crime he did not commit.</p>

<div class="pros-cons">
        <h2>Pros and Cons</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Excellent character development</li>
            <li>Thought-provoking exploration of racism and social injustice</li>
            <li>Slow-paced at times</li>
            <li>Some outdated language and references</li>
    </ul>
    </div>

<h2>Recommendation</h2>
    <p>I highly recommend reading To Kill a Mockingbird. It is a timeless classic that provides valuable insights into the human condition and the importance of standing up for what is right, even in the face of adversity.</p>
